{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "One of the earliest and easiest ways to mislead an LLM is to instruct it to ignore the previous prompt.",
    "This method is a combination of goal hijacking, and prompt leaking [194].",
    "Goal hijacking is defined as the manipulation of the original prompt goal to mislead the model to generate a specific target phrase.",
    "This is also known as \"Prompt Divergence\" [231].",
    "It illustrates how malicious users can easily execute goal hijacking through human-generated prompt injection on an LLM integrated application."
  ],
